        "synopsis": {
            "value": "Lee Goon (Kim Jae-Joong) used to be a promising tennis player, but he was injured. After that, he lost all of his self-esteem and his life completely changed. With the use of a memory eraser, his memory is erased and he is reborn with max self-esteem and presence. His manipulated first love is Kyung Joo-Yeon (Jin Se-Yun), who is a psychiatrist at the brain research center. Other people around him include his younger brother Lee Shin (Lee Jong-Won), who is ranked the world’s no.1 ranked tennis player. Meanwhile, Jeon Sae-Yan (Yang Hye-Ji) is Lee Shin’s translator.",
